library(tidyverse)
library(ggthemes)
library(cowplot)
library(broom)
library(magrittr)
# Macload data set is first 25 specimens of each species
# His figure say petal length/width but I think this is a mistake
# and the actual data is sepal length/width
iris.sepals <- 
  iris %>%
  dplyr::select(-Petal.Length, -Petal.Width) %>%
  group_by(Species) %>%
  group_map(~head(., 25)) %>% 
  ungroup %>%
  mutate_if(is.numeric, scale, center=TRUE, scale=FALSE)
iris.sub <- 
  iris.sepals %>% 
  dplyr::select(-Species) %>% # drop Species column 
  as.matrix  # cast to matrix for calculations  
orig.space.plot <- 
  ggplot(iris.sepals, aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width, color=Species, shape=Species)) + 
  geom_jitter(size=2, height = 0.05, width = 0.05, stroke=1) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette="Set2") +
  scale_shape_discrete(solid=FALSE) +
  labs(x = "Sepal Length\n(Mean centered)", y = "Sepal Width\n(Mean centered)") +
  coord_fixed() + 
  theme(legend.position = "right")
orig.space.plot

pca.all <- prcomp(iris.sepals %>% select(-Species))
pca.all.scores <- 
  as.data.frame(pca.all$x) %>% 
  mutate(Species = iris.sepals$Species)
ggplot(pca.all.scores, aes(PC1, PC2, color=Species)) + 
  geom_point() +
  coord_fixed()

nobs <- nrow(iris.sepals)
ngroups <- nlevels(iris.sepals$Species)
# calculate deviations around grand mean
tot.deviates <-
  iris.sepals %>%
  dplyr::select(-Species) %>%
  mutate_all(funs(. - mean(.))) %>%
  as.matrix
# Total SSQ and covariance matrix
ssq.tot <- t(tot.deviates) %*% tot.deviates
cov.tot <- ssq.tot/nobs  
# calculate deviations around group means
win.deviates <-
  iris.sepals %>%
  group_by(Species) %>%
  mutate_all(funs(. - mean(.))) %>% 
  ungroup %>%
  dplyr::select(-Species) %>%
  as.matrix
`mutate_all()` ignored the following grouping variables:
Column `Species`
Use `mutate_at(df, vars(-group_cols()), myoperation)` to silence the message.
# Within group SSQ and covariance
ssq.win <- t(win.deviates) %*% win.deviates
cov.win <- ssq.win/(nobs - ngroups)
# Between group deviates
btw.deviates <-
  iris.sepals %>% 
  group_by(Species) %>% 
  summarize_all(mean) %>% 
  dplyr::select(-Species) %>% 
  mutate_all(funs(. - mean(.))) %>%
  as.matrix
# Between group SSQ and covariance
ssq.btw <- ngroups * t(btw.deviates) %*% btw.deviates
cov.btw <- ssq.btw/(ngroups-1)
Win.eigen <- eigen(cov.win)
pc1.xend = Win.eigen$vectors[1,1] * 2 * sqrt(Win.eigen$values[1])
pc1.yend = Win.eigen$vectors[2,1] * 2 * sqrt(Win.eigen$values[1])
pc2.xend = Win.eigen$vectors[1,2] * 2 * sqrt(Win.eigen$values[2])
pc2.yend = Win.eigen$vectors[2,2] * 2 * sqrt(Win.eigen$values[2])
orig.space.plot + 
  geom_segment(aes(x=-pc1.xend, y=-pc1.yend, xend=pc1.xend, yend=pc1.yend),
               color='black', alpha=0.5) +
  geom_segment(aes(x=-pc2.xend, y=-pc2.yend, xend=pc2.xend, yend=pc2.yend),
               color='black', alpha=0.5) +
  geom_text(aes(x = pc1.xend*1.15, y = pc1.yend*1.15, label="PC1"), color='black', alpha=0.5) + 
  geom_text(aes(x = pc2.xend*1.15, y = pc2.yend*1.15, label="PC2"), color='black', alpha=0.5)

Win.pc.scores <- iris.sub %*% Win.eigen$vectors
colnames(Win.pc.scores) <- str_c("PC", 1:ncol(iris.sub))
Win.pc.scores.df <- 
  as.data.frame(Win.pc.scores) %>%
  mutate(Species = iris.sepals$Species)
ggplot(Win.pc.scores.df) + 
  aes(x = PC1, y = PC2, color = Species) + 
  geom_point() + 
  coord_fixed()
Win.scale <- diag(1/sqrt(Win.eigen$values))
scaled.Win.pc.scores <- Win.pc.scores %*% Win.scale
colnames(scaled.Win.pc.scores) <- str_c("scaledPC", 1:ncol(iris.sub))  
scaled.Win.pc.scores.df <- 
  as.data.frame(scaled.Win.pc.scores) %>%
  mutate(Species = iris.sepals$Species)
ggplot(scaled.Win.pc.scores.df) + 
  aes(x = scaledPC1, y = scaledPC2, color = Species) + 
  geom_point() + 
  coord_fixed()
scaled.Group.means <-
  scaled.Win.pc.scores.df %>%
  group_by(Species) %>%
  summarize(mean.PC1 = mean(scaledPC1), mean.PC2 = mean(scaledPC2))
  
group.ssqcp <- cov(scaled.Group.means %>% select(-Species)) * (ngroups - 1)
group.eigen <- eigen(group.ssqcp)

group.pc1.xend = group.eigen$vectors[1,1] * sqrt(group.eigen$values[1])
group.pc1.yend = group.eigen$vectors[2,1] * sqrt(group.eigen$values[1])
group.pc2.xend = group.eigen$vectors[1,2] * sqrt(group.eigen$values[2])
group.pc2.yend = group.eigen$vectors[2,2] * sqrt(group.eigen$values[2])

ggplot(scaled.Group.means, aes(x = mean.PC1, y = mean.PC2, color=Species)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_segment(aes(x=-group.pc1.xend, y=-group.pc1.yend, 
                   xend=group.pc1.xend, yend=group.pc1.yend),
               color='black') +
  geom_segment(aes(x=-group.pc2.xend, y=-group.pc2.yend, 
                   xend=group.pc2.xend, yend=group.pc2.yend),
               color='black') +
  geom_text(aes(x = group.pc1.xend*1.1, y = group.pc1.yend*1.1, label="PC1"), color='black') + 
  geom_text(aes(x = group.pc2.xend*1.7, y = group.pc2.yend*1.7, label="PC2"), color='black') + 
  xlim(-4,4) + ylim(-4,4) + 
  coord_fixed()
CVA.scores <- scaled.Win.pc.scores %*% group.eigen$vectors
colnames(CVA.scores) <- str_c("CV", 1:(ngroups-1))
CVA.scores.df <- 
  as.data.frame(CVA.scores) %>%
  mutate(Species = iris.sepals$Species)
ggplot(CVA.scores.df) + 
  aes(x = CV1, y = CV2, color = Species) + 
  geom_point() + 
  coord_fixed()
CVA.scores.in.scaled <- CVA.scores %*% t(group.eigen$vectors)
CVA.axes <- matrix(c(1,0,0,1),nrow=2)
CVA.axes.in.scaled <- CVA.axes %*% t(group.eigen$vectors) %>% set_colnames(c("CV1", "CV2"))

CVA.scores.in.scaled %>% 
  as.data.frame %>% 
  set_colnames(c("scaled.PC1","scaled.PC2")) %>%
  mutate(Species = iris.sepals$Species) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_point(aes(scaled.PC1, scaled.PC2, color=Species)) + 
  geom_segment(data=CVA.axes.in.scaled %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=0,y=0,xend=CV1*3,yend=CV2*3),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) + 
  geom_segment(data=CVA.axes.in.scaled %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=0,y=0,xend=-CV1*3,yend=-CV2*3),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) +  
  geom_text(data=CVA.axes.in.scaled %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=CV1*3.5,y=CV2*3.5, label=c("CV1","CV2")),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) +   
  coord_fixed()
CVA.scores.unscaled <- 
  CVA.scores.in.scaled %*% diag(sqrt(Win.eigen$values)) %>% 
  set_colnames(c("PC1","PC2"))
CVA.axes.unscaled <- 
  CVA.axes.in.scaled %*% diag(sqrt(Win.eigen$values)) %>% 
  set_colnames(c("CV1", "CV2"))

CVA.scores.unscaled %>% 
  as.data.frame %>% 
  mutate(Species = iris.sepals$Species) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_point(aes(PC1, PC2, color=Species)) + 
  geom_segment(data=CVA.axes.unscaled %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=0,y=0,xend=CV1*3,yend=CV2*3),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) + 
  geom_segment(data=CVA.axes.unscaled %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=0,y=0,xend=-CV1*3,yend=-CV2*3),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) +  
  geom_text(data=CVA.axes.unscaled %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=CV1*3.5,y=CV2*3.5, label=c("CV1","CV2")),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) +   
  coord_fixed()
CVA.scores.unscaled.unrotated <- 
  CVA.scores.unscaled %*% t(Win.eigen$vectors) %>% 
  set_colnames(c("Sepal.Length", "Sepal.Width"))
CVA.axes.unscaled.unrotated <- 
  CVA.axes.unscaled %*% t(Win.eigen$vectors) %>% 
  set_colnames(c("CV1", "CV2"))

CVA.scores.unscaled.unrotated %>% 
  as.data.frame %>% 
  mutate(Species = iris.sepals$Species) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_point(aes(Sepal.Length, Sepal.Width, color=Species)) + 
  geom_segment(data=CVA.axes.unscaled.unrotated %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=0,y=0,xend=CV1*3,yend=CV2*3),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) + 
  geom_segment(data=CVA.axes.unscaled.unrotated %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=0,y=0,xend=-CV1*3,yend=-CV2*3),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) +  
  geom_text(data=CVA.axes.unscaled.unrotated %>% as.data.frame,
               mapping = aes(x=CV1*3.5,y=CV2*3.5, label=c("CV1","CV2")),
               inherit.aes = FALSE) +   
  coord_fixed()
# Cacluate the  eigenvectors of W^{-1}B
WinvB = solve(cov.win) %*% cov.btw
eigin.WinvB = eigen(WinvB)

cva.vecs <- Re(eigin.WinvB$vectors)[,1:ngroups-1]
cva.vals <- Re(eigin.WinvB$values)[1:ngroups-1]

unscaled.scores <- win.deviates %*% cva.vecs

# figure out scaling so group covariance matrix is spherical
scaling <- diag(1/sqrt((t(unscaled.scores) %*% unscaled.scores)/(nobs-ngroups)))

# compare to "scaling" component object returned by lda()
scaled.cva.vecs <- cva.vecs %*% diag(scaling) 

cva.scores <- iris.sub %*% scaled.cva.vecs

colnames(cva.scores) <- c("CV1","CV2")
cva.scores <- as.data.frame(cva.scores)
cva.scores$Species <- iris.sepals$Species
ggplot(cva.scores, aes(x = CV1, y = CV2)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color=Species, shape=Species)) + 
  coord_fixed()
